scene.message:
Kurouri: So you're the new{nl}
visitors. Naito told me{nl}
about you.{waitkey}You seem to be having a{nl}
rare experience.{nl}
I'm quite envious.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: ...That's really{nl}
Kurouri? He's talking{nl}
normally, hey!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: He's speaking{nl}
normally... Are you really{nl}
our demon friend?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Hey, where's the{nl}
usual 'hee-hee-hee'?{nl}
That's not like you, demon!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Hey, don't talk{nl}
all normal with{nl}
a face like that!{waitkey}It's even creepier!{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: Hmm...{nl}
The me on the other side{nl}
must be quite the oddball.{waitkey}I'd like to meet him{nl}
someday.{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: Hmm, shall we get{nl}
to the point,{nl}
my visitors?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I hear you've been{nl}
studying the two worlds.{nl}
What do you make of it?{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: Every event in{nl}
this world, though it seems{nl}
unrelated, is bound by{nl}
threads of cause and effect.{waitkey}{clearbox}This black door that{nl}
appeared so suddenly is no{nl}
exception. Only one who{nl}
follows the thread sees truth.{waitkey}{clearbox}And sadly...{nl}
that does not seem to{nl}
be my role to play.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: So our coming here{nl}
was inevitable, and we're{nl}
the ones to uncover it all...{waitkey}is that it?{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: I know not who{nl}
spun the thread, but yes,{nl}
think of it that way.{waitkey}{clearbox}Now then, the name of the{nl}
one who holds the thread's{nl}
end you must follow?{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: Hmm, the name{nl}
I was told. In truth, I knew{nl}
beforehand this would happen.{waitkey}{clearbox}From the prophecy of{nl}
a certain seer I met{nl}
at the shrine...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: A 'monkey' seer?!{nl}
Whoever heard of a{nl}
monkey being a seer!!{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Enough!{nl}
Someone shut that{nl}
monkey up!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: A monkey seer, huh -{nl}
probably Mark's uncle{nl}
or something!{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: Ah, yes...{nl}
He called himself Philemon...{nl}
But more to the point,{waitkey}is this all right?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: It's fine, it's fine.{nl}
Happens all the time!{waitkey}{clearbox}{ctl07:1},{nl}
let's try the Araya Shrine.{waitkey}{clearbox}I've met him before too -{nl}
if it's that man, he might{nl}
know where Kandori is!{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: This door...{nl}
it gives off a{nl}
bad feeling...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Damn!{nl}
I'll settle this{nl}
someday!{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Honestly! Thanks to{nl}
that fool, I forgot what{nl}
I meant to ask.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: The demon of this{nl}
world seems dependable.{nl}
His looks aside, that is.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: The demon, huh...{nl}
It's funny in its own way,{nl}
but it throws me off somehow.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Ehh? Leaving already?{nl}
You're the first guy to drag{nl}
Ayase around this much.{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: With your vitality,{nl}
you'll be fine no matter{nl}
what hardship you meet.{waitkey}A bit noisy, though...{waitkey}{ret}

Yosuke: The Araya Shrine{nl}
is in the same place as{nl}
in our world. Please find{nl}
a way back somehow.{waitkey}{clearbox}And...{wait_fr:60}{nl}
if you meet Chisato,{nl}
please help her. I'm counting{nl}
on you.{waitkey}{ret}

Kurouri: It catches your eye?{nl}
This door appeared all at once{nl}
with the upheaval a month ago.{waitkey}{clearbox}I've tried all sorts of{nl}
things, but it won't{nl}
budge an inch.{waitkey}{clearbox}Well, if the threads of fate{nl}
lead you, the door will{nl}
open in time.{waitkey}{ret}

{color:2}Tsutomu Kurouri.{nl}
An occult nut who's wrong{nl}
about everything...{nl}
or so he should be...{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}
